{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Bader Glacier | other_name = | photo = Ant-pen-map-German.PNG | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Location of German Peninsula in Graham Land, Antarctic Peninsula | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Bader Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[German Peninsula]] | coordinates = {{coord|63|37|S|66|45|W|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Bourgeois Fjord]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
'''Bader Glacier''' ({{Coord|67|37|S|66|45|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a small [[glacier]] draining the west slopes of [[Rudozem Heights]] and flowing to [[Bourgeois Fjord]] just south of [[Thomson Head]] on [[German Peninsula]], [[Fallières Coast]] on the west side of [[Graham Land]], [[Antarctica]]. It was named by the [[UK Antarctic Place-Names Committee]] in 1958 for Swiss glaciologist [[Henri Bader]] of [[Rutgers University]] (U.S.), author of an important thesis on the development of the snowflake and its metamorphoses.
==See also== * [[List of glaciers in the Antarctic]] * [[Glaciology]]
