'''MitoMap''' is a real time [[haplotype|haplotyping]] [[Protocol (science)|protocol]] that analyzes [[pathogen]]ic [[Genetic diversity|variant]]s that cause several [[mitochondria]]l [[disease]]s.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://pharmabiz.com/NewsDetails.aspx?aid=79001&sid=1 | title=SciGenom Labs embarks mitochondria sequencing, reports faster diagnosis of cell diseases}}</ref>  It was carried out [[Real-time data|real-time]] for the first time during the 2013 NexGen [[Genomics]] & [[Bioinformatics]] [[technology|Technologies]] conference at [[Delhi]], [[India]] from November 14–16. The results have been published [[online]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://mitomap.sgrf.org.in | title=MitoMAP Login Page}}</ref>

