{{Infobox scientist | name = Rudolf Stahlecker | image = Rudolf Stahlecker at skull of Scalochrinotherium.jpg | image_size = | caption = | birth_date = 25 November 1898 | birth_place = [[Sternenfels]], Germany | death_date = 26 October 1977 | death_place = [[Bad Urach|Urach]], Germany | residence = | citizenship = | nationality = [[Germany]] | ethnicity = | field = [[paleontologist]] and [[geologist]] | work_institution = [[University of Tübingen]] | alma_mater = | doctoral_advisor = [[Friedrich von Huene]] | doctoral_students = | known_for = | author_abbreviation_bot = | author_abbreviation_zoo = | prizes = | religion = | footnotes = }}
'''Rudolf Stahlecker''' (25 November 1898 in [[Sternenfels]] near [[Pforzheim]] &ndash; 26 October 1977 in [[Bad Urach|Urach]]) was a [[Germans|German]] [[geologist]] and biology teacher.
== Biography ==
He studied with the German [[paleontologist]] [[Friedrich von Huene]] at the [[University of Tübingen]], [[Germany]]. He participated in expeditions to collect fossils in the [[geopark]] of Paleorrota in 1928 and 1929. He also made several collections of fossils in [[Argentina]].
In his honor, the dicynodonts [[Stahleckeria|Stahleckeria potens]], received its name. This [[dicynodont]]s was collected in [[Paleontological Site Chiniquá]], [[São Pedro do Sul, Rio Grande do Sul|São Pedro do Sul]].
After finishing his doctorate, Stahlecker did not become a scientist, but a biology teacher at a school Stuttgart. "The ''Führer'' wants to teach people to think again biologically, we scientists have to be here its first collaborators," was his motto. After The War he had to pause for some years during denazification, although he had not as intensively be involved in National Socialism as his brother, the SS Brigade Leader and Commander of the "Einsatzgruppe A" [[Walter Stahlecker]].<ref>Hans-Joachim Lang: [http://www.tagblatt.de/Home/nachrichten/hochschule_artikel,-Prunkstueck-aus-der-Steinwueste-_arid,55033.html Stahleckeria seit 80 Jahren in der hiesigen Paläontologischen Sammlung] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924112927/http://www.tagblatt.de/Home/nachrichten/hochschule_artikel,-Prunkstueck-aus-der-Steinwueste-_arid,55033.html |date=2015-09-24 }} and [http://www.uni-tuebingen.de/uni/bzf/Presse/SWP-Huene.pdf Prunkstück aus der Steinwüste.] Schwäbisches Tagblatt of 20. Mai 2009 (in German).</ref>
